{
 "_readme": [
  "Ledger of judicious-cutting decisions + budget overrides for the coverage audit.",
  "Consumed by scripts/coverage_lib.py (audit_coverage.py, test_coverage.py).",
  "",
  "defaults: budget applied to every emblem (see coverage_lib.DEFAULTS for meanings).",
  "emblems: per-emblem overrides keyed by emblem number as a string.",
  "  flat: [[x0,y0,x1,y1], ...] normalised rectangles of engraving that is INTENTIONALLY",
  "        left flat on the backing (motto banner, epigram text, plate border). Excluded",
  "        from both the coverage denominator and the gap search \u2014 declaring a region flat",
  "        is you certifying 'this is backing, not a missing cutout'.",
  "  any DEFAULTS key (min_coverage, max_gap_frac, ...) overrides the budget for that emblem.",
  "",
  "The corpus mixes scan types: full-page portrait scans (00-09 at 1200x1434; 11,12,14,20,25",
  "at 705x949) carry motto/epigram/page furniture, declared flat by scripts/declare_page_furniture.py",
  "(auto-detected pictorial frame; rerun after adding plates). Landscape picture-crops are",
  "all-picture, so whole-plate coverage applies and nothing is declared.",
  "",
  "Budgets tightened 2026-07 once page furniture stopped diluting the metric:",
  "observed floor coverage 0.909 / ceiling gap 0.0163 across all 51.",
  "min_figure_coverage > 0 outlaws backdrop-only emblems (every plate needs a real pop)."
